    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# Review Helpfulness Predictor\\n\",\"**NLP Project 79 of 100** — Predict whether a product review is helpful to other customers.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import numpy as np, pandas as pd, matplotlib.pyplot as plt, seaborn as sns\\nfrom sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer\\nfrom sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\\nfrom sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, f1_score, classification_report\\nfrom sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\\nimport warnings; warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\nsns.set_style('whitegrid')\\n%matplotlib inline\\nSEED = 42; rng = np.random.default_rng(SEED)\\nprint('Loaded.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"# Synthetic review data\\nhelpful = ['Great product with excellent build quality. Battery lasts all day. Highly recommend for daily use.',\\n           'Detailed comparison with similar products. This one wins on price and features.',\\n           'I tested this for 3 months. Pros: durable, lightweight. Cons: slightly loud fan.',\\n           'Perfect for beginners. The setup guide is clear and the app works well.'] * 30\\nnot_helpful = ['Good.','Works fine.','ok','Arrived on time.','5 stars!!!','Love it','Nice','meh'] * 30\\n\\ndf = pd.DataFrame({'text': helpful + not_helpful, 'helpful': [1]*len(helpful) + [0]*len(not_helpful)})\\ndf = df.sample(frac=1, random_state=SEED).reset_index(drop=True)\\n\\n# Add features\\ndf['text_len'] = df['text'].str.len()\\ndf['word_count'] = df['text'].str.split().str.len()\\ndf['has_number'] = df['text'].str.contains(r'\\\\d').astype(int)\\nprint(f'Shape: {df.shape}, Helpful rate: {df[\\\"helpful\\\"].mean():.1%}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(df['text'], df['helpful'], test_size=0.2, random_state=SEED)\\ntfidf = TfidfVectorizer(max_features=5000, ngram_range=(1,2))\\nX_tr = tfidf.fit_transform(X_train); X_te = tfidf.transform(X_test)\\n\\nlr = LogisticRegression(max_iter=500, random_state=SEED)\\nlr.fit(X_tr, y_train)\\ny_pred = lr.predict(X_te)\\nprint(f'Accuracy: {accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred):.4f}')\\nprint(f'F1: {f1_score(y_test, y_pred):.4f}')\\nprint(classification_report(y_test, y_pred, target_names=['Not Helpful','Helpful']))\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Summary\\n\",\"- **Review length and detail strongly predict helpfulness.**\\n\",\"- **Short, vague reviews are rarely marked helpful by users.**\\n\",\"- **TF-IDF captures content quality signals effectively.**\\n\",\"- **For production, combine text features with metadata** (rating, reviewer history).\"]}\n",
    " ],\n",
